-- Indian shares end higher; tech stocks gain
-- By Indulal PM
-- Mon Aug 04, 2014 06:07AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Aug 4 (Reuters) - Indian shares ended higher on Monday, snapping two days of falls as software services exporters such as Infosys <INFY.NS> rallied on a weaker rupee while lenders gained a day before the central bank's policy review.

The broader NSE index <.NSEI> provisionally gained 1.12 percent to 7,687.40, while the benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> ended 0.95 percent higher 25,723.16.